    <h1 class="header"> <span class="itemprop" itemprop="name">Changwei Gu</span> 
        
        
    </h1>
    
        <div class="infobar" id="name-job-categories">
            
            
<a href="#cinematographer"
onclick="nameJobCategoriesClickHandler(this)" > <span class="itemprop" itemprop="jobTitle">
Cinematographer</span></a>                 <span class="ghost">|</span> 
            
            
<a href="#director"
onclick="nameJobCategoriesClickHandler(this)" > <span class="itemprop" itemprop="jobTitle">
Director</span></a>                 <span class="ghost">|</span> 
            
            
<a href="#producer"
onclick="nameJobCategoriesClickHandler(this)" > <span class="itemprop" itemprop="jobTitle">
Producer</span></a>            
        </div>
    
        </div>
        </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        
<div class="txt-block" id="name-bio-text">
        <div class="name-trivia-bio-text">
                      <div class="inline" itemprop="description">
Changwei Gu was born on December 12, 1957 in Xi'an, Shaanxi, China. He is a cinematographer and director, known for <a href="/title/tt0106332?ref_=nm_ov_bio_lk1">Farewell My Concubine</a> (1993), <a href="/title/tt0174480?ref_=nm_ov_bio_lk2">Autumn in New York</a> (2000) and <a href="/title/tt1664704?ref_=nm_ov_bio_lk3">Mo shu wai zhuan</a> (2011).            <span class="see-more inline nobr-only">
                    <a href="/name/nm0345146/bio?ref_=nm_ov_bio_sm"
>See full bio</a> &raquo;
            </span>
</div>        </div>
</div>

                        
    <div id="name-born-info" class="txt-block">
        <h4 class="inline">Born:</h4> 
   
  <time datetime="1957-12-12" itemprop="birthDate">
<a href="/search/name?birth_monthday=12-12&refine=birth_monthday&ref_=nm_ov_bth_monthday"
>December 12</a>, 
     
<a href="/search/name?birth_year=1957&ref_=nm_ov_bth_year"
>1957</a>    
  </time>
            in
            <a href="/search/name?birth_place=Xi%27an,+Shaanxi,+China&ref_=nm_ov_bth_place"
>Xi'an, Shaanxi, China</a>
    </div>

                        
                        
                   </td>
